                            <comment id="16521" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Tue, 21 Feb 2006 04:55:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for pointing this out! I&apos;ve fixed MBeanServerConnectionFactoryBean accordingly, tracking the LazyInitTargetSource&apos;s new &quot;isInitialized()&quot; state before calling &quot;close()&quot; on the connector.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Regarding the general issue of destroy methods throwing exceptions: That does not pose a problem, since the BeanFactory will catch and log any exception thrown by a destroy method. Hence, it&apos;s better to throw a cleanup exception and let it be logged rather than catching and swallowing it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
